WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.330
Previously on "Kevin
Saves the World"...

00:04.330 --> 00:05.210
-I'm a messenger from God.
-Oh, good.

00:05.210 --> 00:06.750
I'm here to guide
and protect you.

00:06.750 --> 00:08.250
The only job
you have in life

00:08.250 --> 00:09.380
is to build up
your spiritual powers

00:09.380 --> 00:12.500
through acts of kindness
and selflessness.

00:12.500 --> 00:15.500
God is gonna show you how to
find the other righteous.

00:15.500 --> 00:17.420
I know where we'll find
the first righteous.

00:17.420 --> 00:20.210
Laos.

00:20.210 --> 00:21.120
I don't think
I'd be good company.

00:21.120 --> 00:22.920
That's not possible.

00:22.920 --> 00:27.540
-I met the most amazing woman.

00:27.540 --> 00:29.920
It is.

00:29.920 --> 00:31.830
From now on,
it's all a date.

00:33.620 --> 00:36.380
So, I found this Canadian
website for missed connections.

00:36.380 --> 00:37.120
I'm writing one.

00:53.040 --> 00:54.750
It's her.

00:54.750 --> 00:57.250
"Dear Tyler,

00:57.250 --> 01:00.580
I can't believe it's been so
long since our time together."

01:00.580 --> 01:03.620
♪♪

01:10.040 --> 01:11.920
"Getting e-mails from you
takes me back

01:11.920 --> 01:14.710
to that dance we had in Laos."

01:14.710 --> 01:17.080
Wow. She is so into you.

01:17.080 --> 01:19.620
I think this could be true love.

01:19.620 --> 01:24.080
♪♪

01:24.080 --> 01:26.460
"I have met lots of people
in my travels,

01:26.460 --> 01:29.380
but none as charming as you."

01:29.380 --> 01:33.790
She called you charming.
High praise indeed, my good man.

01:33.790 --> 01:37.710
"I only wish we didn't live
so far away."

01:37.710 --> 01:41.210
"I've never been good at
long-distance relationships"...

01:41.210 --> 01:44.080
Oh, no.
That doesn't sound good.

01:44.080 --> 01:46.460
She's laying the groundwork
to brush you off.

01:46.460 --> 01:49.000
Only a matter of time
before she

01:49.000 --> 01:51.120
Don't you listen
to that milk.

01:51.120 --> 01:53.920
You know
how I really feel.

01:53.920 --> 01:57.750
-You're here.
-Yes. I am.

01:59.250 --> 02:02.330
Hmm. "I worry that our lives
are too different.

02:02.330 --> 02:04.290
We have
different interests.

02:04.290 --> 02:06.620
Maybe we should
just say goodbye."

02:06.620 --> 02:08.670
Well, that doesn't sound good.

02:08.670 --> 02:11.920
But read between
the lines.

02:11.920 --> 02:14.250
What am I
really saying?

02:14.250 --> 02:16.540
-That if I want this to work...
-Mm.

02:16.540 --> 02:18.500
...I'm gonna have to
work harder.
Mm-hmm.

02:18.500 --> 02:20.960
'Cause something this great
doesn't come that easy.

02:20.960 --> 02:24.000
You...are...right.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.080
Now eat.

02:26.080 --> 02:28.540
You need your strength

02:28.540 --> 02:31.080
if we're gonna be together
forever.

02:34.710 --> 02:36.670
What the hell
are you doing?

02:37.920 --> 02:40.540
Moron.
Pay attention.

02:44.670 --> 02:46.380
Stop eating
the customer's food.

02:47.000 --> 02:47.750
♪♪

02:56.710 --> 03:00.710
♪♪

03:04.210 --> 03:08.250
♪♪

03:11.670 --> 03:14.380
Why -- wh--
why are you pulling over?

03:14.380 --> 03:16.380
Didn't you see that guy
back there? He needs a lift.

03:16.380 --> 03:18.210
Are you out of your mind?

03:18.210 --> 03:20.210
No one stops
for hitchhikers anymore.

03:20.210 --> 03:22.830
I know.
That's why I'm doing it.

03:22.830 --> 03:25.080
Uh-- no.
I'm responsible for your safety.

03:25.080 --> 03:26.790
I cannot --

03:27.580 --> 03:28.790
I'm not.

03:29.460 --> 03:31.080
But I can.

03:32.670 --> 03:34.580
This is great.

03:34.580 --> 03:36.170
Yep.

03:37.500 --> 03:39.420
No one's
getting murdered.

03:41.330 --> 03:44.460
He seems nice.
Can you just stop talking?

03:44.460 --> 03:46.170
Hey, man, you all right?

03:46.170 --> 03:48.540
Yes. Yes. Yes, I am.

03:48.540 --> 03:51.670
I'm, uh -- I'm very --
very all right.

03:51.670 --> 03:53.120
I was just thinking about,

03:53.120 --> 03:57.040
you know, how everybody thinks
the world is so dangerous,

03:57.040 --> 04:00.080
but, you know, there are
nice people out there, too.

04:00.080 --> 04:03.420
Okay?
They're not killers.

04:03.420 --> 04:05.290
They're not people
who are gonna rob you

04:05.290 --> 04:07.500
and leave your body
in the dirt.

04:07.500 --> 04:09.330
Everybody's nice.
Everybody's friends.

04:09.330 --> 04:10.880
-Here's good.

04:10.880 --> 04:13.080
You -- you can -- you can
just let me out right here.

04:13.080 --> 04:15.330
Oh. No, no, no, no, no.
I thought you --
Please?

04:15.330 --> 04:16.750
-Just let me out.

04:16.750 --> 04:18.880
-Are you --
-Please.

04:18.880 --> 04:20.330
I hope you're happy.

04:20.330 --> 04:21.830
What is wrong with you?

04:21.830 --> 04:22.920
Nothing's wrong with me.

04:22.920 --> 04:24.330
You were raising your voice
to me first.

04:24.330 --> 04:25.790
-Let me out!
-No, no, no, no.

04:25.790 --> 04:28.460
No, no, no...okay.
-Let me out! Please.

04:28.460 --> 04:30.000
All right. You're fine,
you're fine, you're fine.

04:30.000 --> 04:33.500
-You're crazy, man.
-I was -- I was defending you!

04:39.500 --> 04:41.580
Kevin: He thought
I was the crazy one.

04:41.580 --> 04:43.460
Um, you are.

04:43.460 --> 04:45.790
Do you know any sane person who
would've stopped for that man?

04:45.790 --> 04:48.500
I have a warrior for God
protecting me.

04:48.500 --> 04:51.250
Unh-unh. You weren't thinking
about that when you pulled over.

04:52.500 --> 04:54.880
Oh, yeah. I guess not.

04:54.880 --> 04:56.580
It just seemed like
the right thing to do.

04:59.460 --> 05:01.380
You've changed.

05:01.380 --> 05:03.040
More than I realized.

05:03.040 --> 05:05.420
I'm not the old me.

05:05.420 --> 05:07.710
That guy is long gone.

05:07.710 --> 05:09.580
Tyler: Ooh, ha-ha.

05:09.580 --> 05:11.670
Look who's the newest member
of the clean-plate club.

05:11.670 --> 05:14.460
Quick question.

05:14.460 --> 05:17.040
Are you a fan
of Teutonic thrash metal?

05:17.040 --> 05:20.460
I...
I don't...think so?

05:20.460 --> 05:22.670
-I'm trying to get into it.

05:22.670 --> 05:25.120
My lady's a big fan
of German scream-singing.

05:27.420 --> 05:29.880
Ahh.
Your

05:29.880 --> 05:31.170
Yeah, my lady from Laos.

05:32.710 --> 05:34.080
Been in communicado.

05:34.080 --> 05:35.170
Oh...

05:35.170 --> 05:38.120
Deep communicado.

05:38.120 --> 05:41.000
Wow.
You

05:41.000 --> 05:42.460
She found me.

05:42.460 --> 05:45.210
She lives in
Victoria, British Columbia.

05:45.210 --> 05:47.120
Even her name
sounds Canadian.

05:47.120 --> 05:48.540
Leslie.

05:50.460 --> 05:51.790
Leslie Nielsen.

05:51.790 --> 05:52.830
What?

05:52.830 --> 05:56.080
That's...crazy, Ty. Wow.

05:56.080 --> 05:58.000
Leslie Nielsen.

05:58.000 --> 05:59.580
-We've been e-mailing a bunch.
-No, no, no.

05:59.580 --> 06:01.420
I'm not e-mailing anybody.

06:01.420 --> 06:05.120
Every e-mail I get from her,
she becomes more interesting.

06:05.120 --> 06:07.670
-Huh.
-So great, man.

06:07.670 --> 06:11.170
Whoa.
Don't leave the hammer hanging.

06:11.170 --> 06:13.790
Oh. Sorry.

06:13.790 --> 06:16.920
Oh. Been doing
some arts and crafts?

06:18.210 --> 06:20.880
Uh, I'm s-sorry about that.

06:20.880 --> 06:23.460
I...don't know
how that happened.

06:23.460 --> 06:25.540
Oh, no.
Dude, I love secrets.

06:25.540 --> 06:27.790
Who likes explanations?
Not this guy.

06:29.710 --> 06:33.710
♪♪

06:36.880 --> 06:39.670
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

06:39.670 --> 06:41.250
We have an imposter.

06:41.250 --> 06:42.960
Someone's pretending
to be me.

06:42.960 --> 06:44.580
Leslie Nielsen.

06:44.580 --> 06:46.580
As me.

06:46.580 --> 06:47.920
Well, whoever it is,

06:47.920 --> 06:50.210
they must've seen
Tyler's post looking for you.

06:50.210 --> 06:51.580
Well, I'm putting
an end to it.

06:51.580 --> 06:54.330
What -- what are you --
what are you gonna do?

06:54.330 --> 06:56.290
Mm. That's above your pay grade.
Don't you worry about it.

06:56.290 --> 06:58.620
Okay.

06:58.620 --> 07:00.620
And why are you
such a mess today?

07:00.620 --> 07:01.960
Hm?

07:06.170 --> 07:08.080
I don't --
I don't know.

07:14.460 --> 07:16.380
I think I'm getting
a, uh, sign.

07:17.790 --> 07:20.830
I will break that hand.

07:22.500 --> 07:24.710
Okay.
I need to go pick up Reese.

07:24.710 --> 07:28.170
So I'm...gonna...

07:28.170 --> 07:33.710
♪♪

07:33.710 --> 07:36.040
Amy: Put your papers at the end
of the desk, please.

07:38.210 --> 07:41.920
Sorry. Excuse me.
Excuse me.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.880
How you doing?
All right.

07:47.080 --> 07:48.500
-Hey.
-Hey.

07:48.500 --> 07:51.500
Wha
You're not my student.

07:51.500 --> 07:53.830
I just had a minute.
Just stopping by.
Aww.

07:53.830 --> 07:55.250
Hey, do you remember
Bobby Sackett?

07:55.250 --> 07:58.040
Uh, yeah. Of course.

07:58.040 --> 08:00.120
His sister gave me chickenpox
senior year in high school.

08:00.120 --> 08:01.830
Well, uh,
he's getting married finally.

08:01.830 --> 08:03.460
Um, I don't know,

08:03.460 --> 08:04.790
you want to go to his wedding
with me this Saturday?

08:04.790 --> 08:07.250
Sure. That sounds fun.

08:07.250 --> 08:09.880
Well, it...could be.

08:09.880 --> 08:12.460
You should know
Simone is gonna be there.

08:12.460 --> 08:14.330
Oh.

08:14.330 --> 08:16.080
I-I thought
Simone moved to Houston.

08:16.080 --> 08:18.000
Yeah, she's -- she's coming
back in town for the wedding.

08:18.000 --> 08:19.380
-Oh.
You know what?

08:19.380 --> 08:20.960
It's probably too weird
to go to a wedding

08:20.960 --> 08:22.080
where my ex-wife
is gonna be.

08:22.080 --> 08:23.500
We should just
forget about it, right?

08:23.500 --> 08:26.040
No, no. I mean, I don't --
I don't think it's weird.

08:26.040 --> 08:29.790
I like Simone. She's cool.
You're cool. I'm real cool.

08:29.790 --> 08:30.710
It'll be fine.

08:30.710 --> 08:32.670
Yeah, I guess.

08:37.420 --> 08:39.120
-As long as you are.
-I am. I'm good.

08:39.120 --> 08:40.380
Then, yeah, I'm good.

08:40.380 --> 08:41.170
-Okay.
-Okay.

08:44.710 --> 08:46.670
♪♪

08:46.670 --> 08:47.790
Kevin: How's it going?

08:49.960 --> 08:51.250
Are you
one of those people

08:51.250 --> 08:54.210
who craves attention
no matter what?

08:54.210 --> 08:57.080
Are you
one of those people who...

08:57.080 --> 08:58.210
likes the smell
of dirty socks?

08:58.210 --> 08:59.830
No. No. Stop. No.

09:03.960 --> 09:06.000
Oh, no, no.

09:10.790 --> 09:12.250
Let me just...

09:14.250 --> 09:18.210
Have you checked the oil
recently?

09:18.210 --> 09:19.960
Yeah, Reese.

09:19.960 --> 09:22.170
I checked the oil,

09:22.170 --> 09:25.040
because that is totally
something that I would do.

09:31.880 --> 09:34.330
What are --

09:34.330 --> 09:39.500
♪♪

09:39.500 --> 09:44.710
♪♪

09:44.710 --> 09:45.620
What are you doing?

09:48.960 --> 09:53.040
Reese, do you want to help me
paint a house?

09:53.040 --> 09:55.670
Are you kidding?
I have homework.

09:55.670 --> 10:01.000
♪♪

10:01.000 --> 10:03.120
It doesn't look good!

10:05.250 --> 10:06.420
What'd you say?

10:06.420 --> 10:12.250
♪♪

10:12.250 --> 10:15.120
You can see
all your brushstrokes.

10:15.120 --> 10:18.080
Looks terrible.
-Maybe I want to.

10:18.080 --> 10:20.170
And maybe it's because
I'm using a brush.

10:20.170 --> 10:22.120
-Hey.

10:22.120 --> 10:23.120
Is this your house?

10:24.540 --> 10:26.000
No.

10:26.000 --> 10:27.460
Is it

10:27.460 --> 10:29.080
No.

10:29.080 --> 10:31.120
Can I help you?

10:31.120 --> 10:33.380
-Hi. Uh, we were just --
-Wow.

10:33.380 --> 10:36.250
You painted my house?
That's incredible.

10:36.250 --> 10:38.000
-Thanks.

10:38.000 --> 10:39.540
No. I've never seen her
in my life.

10:40.750 --> 10:42.580
I think
that was the Acorn Fairy.

10:42.580 --> 10:45.170
-It's, like, this local legend.

10:45.170 --> 10:47.750
Somebody's been going
around town, fixing things,

10:47.750 --> 10:49.750
but no one can figure out
who it is.

10:49.750 --> 10:51.040
Man:
You missed a spot here,

10:51.040 --> 10:53.290
and a lot of --
a lot of visible brushstrokes.

10:53.290 --> 10:55.290
[ Engine starts,
tires screeching ]

10:55.290 --> 10:59.290
♪♪

11:02.960 --> 11:04.670
Do you want to meet her?

11:04.670 --> 11:05.880
Kind of.

11:05.880 --> 11:06.960
Okay, let's go.

11:06.960 --> 11:08.710
Man: You'll finish the job,
right?

11:08.710 --> 11:11.080
Just -- yeah, just come on back
later. That's great.

11:15.460 --> 11:17.620
Tell me about this...
lawn gnome.

11:17.620 --> 11:19.080
Acorn Fairy.

11:19.080 --> 11:20.830
Acorn Fairy,
I was gonna say.

11:20.830 --> 11:22.880
Like 10 years ago,

11:22.880 --> 11:26.420
some mystery person started
fixing things around town,

11:26.420 --> 11:31.080
like, planting flowers in parks
and patching people's roofs.

11:31.080 --> 11:32.120
And there's always,
like,

11:32.120 --> 11:35.040
a little stenciled acorn
left behind.

11:35.040 --> 11:38.500
-Hmm.
-It's funny.

11:38.500 --> 11:40.460
When I was little,
I kind of thought

11:40.460 --> 11:43.670
it was an actually fairy,
not a real person.

11:43.670 --> 11:45.540
Kids are dumb.

11:50.500 --> 11:51.790
She pretty much does
what you do.

11:51.790 --> 11:53.250
She helps people.

11:53.250 --> 11:56.500
Hm. Then I guess
she's pretty cool.

11:56.500 --> 12:00.330
You're like a lame version
of the Acorn Fairy.

12:00.330 --> 12:01.710
Psht.

12:06.040 --> 12:08.210
Some really mean dogs in here.

12:11.380 --> 12:13.170
My uncle helps people.

12:13.170 --> 12:19.120
He handed out money around town
and put up a local art show.

12:21.330 --> 12:23.790
And he bought computers
for the school.

12:26.580 --> 12:28.000
That was you?

12:28.000 --> 12:30.210
Uh, guilty as charged.

12:30.210 --> 12:31.540
That was
some pretty solid work.

12:31.540 --> 12:33.670
Thanks.

12:33.670 --> 12:35.120
Also, you dropped this.

12:37.250 --> 12:40.250
Well, I started helping people
'cause I got bored.

12:40.250 --> 12:43.580
I retired
and needed a hobby.

12:43.580 --> 12:47.290
But why don't you want
anyone to know who you are?

12:47.290 --> 12:50.330
'Cause people get weird
when you help them.

12:50.330 --> 12:53.790
They, uh -- they always feel
a need to repay you.

12:53.790 --> 12:57.500
-Mm.
-That's not what I want.

12:57.500 --> 13:02.250
All this Acorn Fairy crap came
from this mailbox I fixed once.

13:02.250 --> 13:05.380
I painted a little acorn on it
'cause I thought it was cute.

13:05.380 --> 13:09.380
-Aww.
-The Acorn Fairy was born.

13:09.380 --> 13:12.210
-Hello, there.
-Oh, Roscoe.

13:12.210 --> 13:14.620
I find strays
and foster them here.

13:14.620 --> 13:17.000
That sounds...cozy.

13:17.000 --> 13:18.290
Can't help myself.

13:18.290 --> 13:19.500
You know,
I nurse them back to health

13:19.500 --> 13:21.210
and find them
a good home.

13:21.210 --> 13:23.290
And how many dogs
do you have?

13:23.290 --> 13:26.880
Well, at the moment,
I only have seven.

13:26.880 --> 13:30.040
Well, that sounds like a good
amount for this Airstream.

13:30.040 --> 13:31.750
Ah, I wish
I could have more.

13:31.750 --> 13:33.420
I'd love to buy
the lot next door,

13:33.420 --> 13:35.960
put my own Animal Rescue
on it.

13:35.960 --> 13:38.620
But I don't have $60,000
lying around.

13:38.620 --> 13:41.380
-Ah, yeah.
-You should help her.

13:41.380 --> 13:43.540
You're right.
Yes, I should.

13:43.540 --> 13:46.250
As a little
professional courtesy.

13:46.250 --> 13:47.670
You got that kind of money?

13:47.670 --> 13:49.040
Um, well, no.

13:49.040 --> 13:50.920
Um, that's something
to consider.

13:50.920 --> 13:52.210
But I, um...

13:52.210 --> 13:54.790
Ow. God.

13:54.790 --> 13:58.120
That's -- Good point.
Um, I will, um --

13:58.120 --> 13:59.750
I'll think
of something.

13:59.750 --> 14:01.710
So big.

14:01.710 --> 14:04.120
Amy, Is that you?

14:04.120 --> 14:06.750
Wow. Simone. Hi.

14:06.750 --> 14:08.830
Um --
-Great to see you.

14:08.830 --> 14:10.040
I heard
you were in town.

14:10.040 --> 14:11.670
I...

14:11.670 --> 14:13.710
Dating my ex-husband
looks good on you.

14:13.710 --> 14:15.920
Oh my God,
don't make that face.

14:15.920 --> 14:18.210
I...
I talked to Nate.

14:18.210 --> 14:19.670
He seems really happy,

14:19.670 --> 14:22.670
which makes me happy,
so...

14:22.670 --> 14:24.920
...can we just not be all weird
and awkward about it?

14:24.920 --> 14:28.000
Yes. Please.
That would be just so great.

14:28.000 --> 14:29.580
-Yay, normal people.

14:29.580 --> 14:32.170
Except I kind of want to
kill you right now

14:32.170 --> 14:33.500
'cause you look
exactly the same.

14:33.500 --> 14:36.580
Oh, come on, you look amazing.
What have you been up to?

14:36.580 --> 14:38.500
Actually...

14:38.500 --> 14:41.120
Wow. That's...

14:41.120 --> 14:43.540
-It's fast, I know. It's just...
-No. I mean, whatever.

14:43.540 --> 14:45.290
I mean, it's faster
than I planned.

14:45.290 --> 14:47.500
I mean, so is being pregnant.

14:47.500 --> 14:49.540
Wow.

14:49.540 --> 14:52.210
Oh, my -- Just listen to me.
All I keep saying is "wow."

14:52.210 --> 14:54.210
So do I.

14:54.210 --> 14:55.880
-Awful.

14:55.880 --> 14:57.960
Just all-day nausea.

14:57.960 --> 15:00.210
But I'm really happy.

15:01.790 --> 15:04.710
Simone, that is so amazing.
I'm so happy for you.

15:04.710 --> 15:06.710
-Thanks. Um, I got to run...
-Okay.

15:06.710 --> 15:08.120
...but I'll see you
at the rehearsal dinner, right?

15:08.120 --> 15:09.750
Yes. Definitely.

15:09.750 --> 15:12.170
Definitely.

15:12.170 --> 15:15.080
♪♪

15:15.080 --> 15:18.210
Kevin:
How nice is Phoebe?

15:18.210 --> 15:20.290
And her dream
is to help animals?

15:20.290 --> 15:23.000
I mean,
I'm a righteous person,

15:23.000 --> 15:25.880
and all my dreams
involve mixing foods

15:25.880 --> 15:27.960
that don't normally
go together.

15:27.960 --> 15:31.120
So, uh, what do you plan
on doing for her?

15:31.120 --> 15:33.330
I don't know.
Maybe a telethon

15:33.330 --> 15:37.250
or a dance...athon?

15:37.250 --> 15:38.710
Any kind of thon,
really.

15:38.710 --> 15:40.920
Phoebe clearly doesn't want
that sort of recognition.

